==English==
===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/stɪnt/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪnt|-ɪnt]]

===Etymology 1===
Old English ''[[styntan]]'' ‘make blunt’, probably influenced in some senses by cognate Old Norse ''*stynta''.

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{cattag|archaic|intransitive}} To [[stop]] (an action); [[cease]], [[desist]].
# {{cattag|obsolete|intransitive}} To stop speaking or talking (of a subject).
#*'''Late C14''': Now wol I '''stynten''' of this Arveragus, / And speken I wole of Dorigen his wyf — Geoffrey Chaucer, ‘The Franklin's Tale’, ''Canterbury Tales''
# {{intransitive}} To be [[sparing]] or [[mean]].
#:''The next party you throw, don't '''stint''' on the beer.''

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A [[period]] of [[time]].
#:''He had a '''stint''' in jail.''

===Etymology 2===
Origin unknown.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# Any of several very small [[wading bird]]s in the genus ''[[Calidris]]''.

